<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include("./partials/head") %>
  <title>Privacy Policy - Zipply</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/privacy.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <%- include("./partials/nav") %>

  <main class="privacy">
    <div class="privacy__container">
      <h1 class="privacy__title">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Zipply collects, uses, and protects your data.</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect the following information when you use Zipply:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email and name (during signup)</li>
        <li>URLs you shorten</li>
        <li>Click data: timestamps, visit counts</li>
        <li>QR Code you generate along with timestamps</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <p>Your data is used to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Track analytics and usage patterns</li>
        <li>Provide link history and dashboard stats</li>
        <li>Track QR Code History</li>

      </ul>

      <h2>3. Data Storage & Security</h2>
      <p>We use secure databases (MongoDB) and JWT authentication to protect user data. Passwords are stored in hashed format.</p>

      <h2>4. Third-Party Sharing</h2>
      <p>Zipply does <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties.</p>

      <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
      <p>Zipply does not use any cookies to track users. All sessions and tokens are handled securely using JWT.</p>

      <h2>6. Data Deletion</h2>
      <p>You can request account deletion by contacting the developer, and your data will be permanently erased.</p>

      <p class="privacy__footer-note">This policy was last updated by <strong>Aman Show</strong>. For privacy-related questions, contact via GitHub or LinkedIn.</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include("./partials/footer") %>
  <%- include("./partials/scripts") %>
</body>
</html>
